3. Approaches Tried
3.1 Athena Console - Direct Query
Attempted to query the cross-account Glue catalog directly from the Athena Query Editor in our AWS Console.
	•	Ran SHOW TABLES IN "glue:767397940910".fdk_uk_customer_db_iceberg
	•	Got syntax error - Athena does not support inline cross-account catalog references
	•	Tried with backticks: SHOW TABLES IN `glue.767397940910`.fdk_uk_customer_db_iceberg
	•	Got error: Catalog 'glue.767397940910' does not exist
Result: Failed - Cross-account catalog not registered as a data source in Athena.
3.2 Athena Console - Register Cross-Account Data Source
Registered the cross-account Glue catalog as an Athena Data Source.
	•	Went to Athena > Data Sources > Create Data Source
	•	Selected "S3 - AWS Glue Data Catalogue"
	•	Entered Catalog ID: 767397940910
	•	Data source created successfully as "Athena-9f3ddi0k"
	•	Ran: SHOW TABLES IN `Athena-9f3ddi0k`.fdk_uk_customer_db_iceberg
	•	Associated databases showed 0 - no databases visible
Result: Failed - Data source registered but no access. Our IAM user identity does not have cross-account Glue permissions. The target account has not granted access via a Glue resource policy.
3.3 Managed Flink Application - Glue SDK Direct Access
Built a Java Flink application that uses the AWS Glue SDK v2 to call GetDatabase and GetTables directly on the cross-account catalog.
	•	Created Maven project with Flink 1.18, AWS SDK v2 (Glue, S3, STS, UrlConnectionHttpClient)
	•	Built fat JAR using maven-shade-plugin, uploaded to S3
	•	Deployed to Managed Flink app "DB-testing-app" with role svc-role-real-time-transformation-poc
	•	Flink app started successfully and executed the Glue API calls
	•	Results written to s3://flink-poc-app-nishikesh/output/glue-table-list-result.txt
	•	Got AccessDeniedException from Glue API for both fdk_ and fdp_ database variants
Result: Partially Successful - The Flink application deployed, ran, and made the correct Glue API calls to catalog 767397940910. However, access was denied by the target account.
