6. Current Blocker
All approaches fail with AccessDeniedException. The error from the Flink output confirms:
User: arn:aws:sts::739275465799:assumed-role/svc-role-real-time-transformation-poc/kiam-flink is not authorized to perform: glue:GetDatabase on resource: arn:aws:glue:eu-west-1:767397940910:...
This means our role has the correct IAM permissions (glue:Get* on Resource: "*") on our side, but the target account (767397940910) has not granted access via a Glue catalog resource policy.
Cross-account Glue access requires both sides to have the correct permissions: our role needs glue:Get* (which it has), AND the target account needs a resource policy on their Glue catalog allowing our role.
7. Action Required from Target Account Team
The team managing account 767397940910 (ADP/EDB team - contact: Amol) needs to add the following Glue Catalog Resource Policy on their Glue catalog in eu-west-1:
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [{
    "Effect": "Allow",
    "Principal": {
      "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::739275465799:role/svc-role-real-time-transformation-poc"
    },
    "Action": ["glue:GetDatabase","glue:GetDatabases","glue:GetTable",
               "glue:GetTables","glue:GetPartitions"],
    "Resource": [
      "arn:aws:glue:eu-west-1:767397940910:catalog",
      "arn:aws:glue:eu-west-1:767397940910:database/fdk_uk_customer_db_iceberg",
      "arn:aws:glue:eu-west-1:767397940910:table/fdk_uk_customer_db_iceberg/*"
    ]
  }]
}
